The paper deals with statistical inference and information processing of high-dimensional data, which is a common theme in the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), computer vision (cs.CV), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper specifically focuses on covariance estimation, which is a key problem in many of these sub-fields. The use of convex programming and restricted isometry properties also suggests a strong connection to the sub-categories of optimization (cs.OC) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). However, given the emphasis on statistical inference and covariance estimation, we believe that the aforementioned five sub-categories are the most likely.
